President Donald J. Trump met with Iraqi Prime Minister Haider al-Abadi to reaffirm America's support for Iraq in the fight against ISIS. They discussed the close bonds between the American and Iraqi people and the importance of the relationship between the two governments. They praised the cooperation between the United States and Iraq in the fight against ISIS and agreed to pursue a long-term partnership to root out terrorism from Iraq and strengthen the Iraqi military. They also discussed promoting a broad-based political and economic partnership, deepening commercial ties, and promoting investment and collaboration in the energy sector. The United States commended Iraq's efforts to foster positive relations with regional partners and emphasized the importance of stability in the Middle East. The United States and Iraq are committed to a comprehensive and mutually beneficial partnership.